msIdentifier.repository: Khedivial Library, today: Egyptian National Library and Archives (دار الكتب والوثائق القومية) , Cairo

summary.p: Fragments of a Qurʾān codex on parchment; The precise amount of leaves is unknown, accessible photos of this entry contain some 180 different pages (of some pages several images are available); Shelfmark: "qāf 4"; 7 lines per page; Dimensions: unknown; Accessible images contain the following text ranges: Q 2:152-160, Q 4:113-114, Q 4:128 - Q 5:3, Q 5:15-91, Q 15:4-40, Q 25:5-18, Q 43:89 - Q 44:44, Q 45:25 - Q 46:10, Q 51:12 - Q 53:62, 54:1-43, Q 55:7-68, Q 56:12-41; Script style: kūfī D. I/D. III; Estimated date of production: 750-900 (3rd/9th century according to B. Moritz). The Album Arabic Palaeography of Bernhard Moritz, Cairo in 1905, contains two images of this Qur'an codex with the title : "Kurʾān. III cent. Khedivial Library" (Moritz 1905, pl. 37-38).

The call number "qāf 4" is given for the available images, because it is used by Gotthelf Bergsträßer who presumably took the photos around 1930 in Cairo. The number of images in this entry is given for technical reasons, and the given number does not indicate folio numbers. For three images no. 7, 125 and 200, no text range could be suggested so far. Image no. 162 of "qāf 4" corresponds to table 37 in Moritz, image no. 170 corresponds to table 38.
